Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.52,0:00:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.92,0:00:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Let's talk about designing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.36,0:00:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,glyphs, and I think a good place
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.57,0:00:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to start is what is a glyph?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.54,0:00:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A glyph, traditionally, is a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.92,0:00:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,topographical character, but it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.40,0:00:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,could also be a symbol or a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.38,0:00:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,simple shape of a real world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.89,0:00:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,object, or it can be a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.96,0:00:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,combination of shapes to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.96,0:00:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,represent function or a concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.14,0:00:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But you might be thinking what
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.05,0:00:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is the difference between this
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.67,0:00:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and an icon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.06,0:00:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to help illustrate the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.50,0:00:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,difference, let's take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.01,0:00:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this example of four iPhone
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.48,0:00:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,icons.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.01,0:00:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,An icon can refer to a broad set
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.10,0:00:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of assets ranging from simple
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.52,0:00:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,low fidelity shapes like you can
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.83,0:01:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,see on the left to illustrative,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.92,0:01:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,colorful, and highly rendered
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.76,0:01:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,assets that you can see on the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.26,0:01:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.80,0:01:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The two assets on the left can
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.16,0:01:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,also be defined as glyphs, and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.87,0:01:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that's because of their
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.37,0:01:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,simplicity, and for the most
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.43,0:01:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,part, glyphs are monochromatic
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.68,0:01:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and should be colorized
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.69,0:01:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,programmatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.84,0:01:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the iOS wallet app icon,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.56,0:01:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can see a nice use of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.70,0:01:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,color and some subtle shading.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.00,0:01:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's the app represented
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.78,0:01:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,as a glyph.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.64,0:01:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you get the idea, but let's
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.56,0:01:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,take a look at one more example.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.71,0:01:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the phone app icon, and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.58,0:01:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,if we take away that iconic
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.95,0:01:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,shape and the color, you see
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.85,0:01:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,where I'm going with this, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.81,0:01:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,left with this glyph.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.64,0:01:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in this case, the glyph is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.47,0:01:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,actually part of what makes up
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.59,0:01:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the icon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.64,0:01:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, effective glyphs have some
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.84,0:01:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,key characteristics.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.91,0:02:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're highly simplified in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,form.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.00,0:02:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They're conceptually universal,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.88,0:02:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're quickly readable in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.27,0:02:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,context as to their function or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.05,0:02:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.30,0:02:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of us have experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.61,0:02:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,being in a foreign place,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.64,0:02:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere where we don't, you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.97,0:02:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,know, relate to the culture or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.40,0:02:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,another language, and it can be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.75,0:02:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,quite a relief when we see a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.70,0:02:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,symbol that we recognize.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.87,0:02:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in this case, you don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.95,0:02:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to know German to know the right
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.11,0:02:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,way to the airport, and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.02,0:02:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,thanks to this simple universal
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.79,0:02:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,shape, which in this context we
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.55,0:02:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,understand to represent airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.22,0:02:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, glyphs are a powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.01,0:02:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,communication tool, and that's
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.13,0:02:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,why we make them part of our
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.16,0:02:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,design language in UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.44,0:02:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's go through a quick
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.59,0:02:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,exercise to conceptualize an
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.78,0:02:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,effective glyph.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.71,0:02:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say we need one to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.76,0:03:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,represent delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.90,0:03:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing you might think
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.92,0:03:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of is a cheeseburger, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.77,0:03:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,would have no argument from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.83,0:03:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I do think cheeseburgers are
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.05,0:03:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.32,0:03:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,But believe it or not, some
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.49,0:03:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,people do not like
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.73,0:03:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,cheeseburgers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.26,0:03:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what's better than a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.80,0:03:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,cheeseburger?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.82,0:03:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Pizza? I see some people shaking
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.72,0:03:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,their heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.06,0:03:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.87,0:03:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. I think I got one that we
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.84,0:03:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,can all relate to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.27,0:03:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How about ice cream?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.59,0:03:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Well, all right, well, I
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.07,0:03:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,think I could -- you got the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.34,0:03:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,idea here -- not everyone
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.25,0:03:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,relates to these specific food
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.78,0:03:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,items in the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.12,0:03:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, these aren't effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.08,0:03:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's try something a little
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.22,0:03:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,bit different, and what about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.91,0:03:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,something to get to the core of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.17,0:03:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,what delicious might make us
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.17,0:03:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Something like a facial
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.09,0:03:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.16,0:03:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's cute and relatable,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.61,0:03:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,expressive, but we should be
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.05,0:03:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,mindful here that in some
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.11,0:04:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,cultures using like a face, a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.07,0:04:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,mouth, or a body part can be
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.93,0:04:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,seen as inappropriate; so, be
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.54,0:04:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,mindful of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.33,0:04:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what is a universal symbol
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.22,0:04:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for delicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.17,0:04:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What about a heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.55,0:04:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We love cheeseburgers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.63,0:04:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people like pizza.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.46,0:04:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people love ice cream.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.13,0:04:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The association of love with
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.09,0:04:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,delicious is much more universal
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.78,0:04:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,than our other options.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.18,0:04:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is a nice effective
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.18,0:04:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.99,0:04:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, let's take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.37,0:04:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,some examples of where we use
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.28,0:04:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,glyphs on our platforms, on the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.69,0:04:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Mac, in the menu bar, in tool
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.42,0:04:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,bars, and in sidebars, and most
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.13,0:04:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,recently, in the touch bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.12,0:04:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,On iOS, in tab bars, list views,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.68,0:05:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and home screen quick action
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.07,0:05:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,menus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.88,0:05:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can see, glyphs are
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.25,0:05:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,everywhere, and also notice that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.83,0:05:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they rarely ever stand alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.08,0:05:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's why we need to be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.75,0:05:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,mindful of some design
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.69,0:05:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,considerations when, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.87,0:05:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,we're crafting a set of glyphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.56,0:05:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Our goal should be to make them
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.70,0:05:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,feel like a family, and a family
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.65,0:05:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,has a shared set of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.54,0:05:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,characteristics.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.73,0:05:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're going to look at
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.32,0:05:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,optical weight, lines, and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.11,0:05:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,positioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.59,0:05:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In this example, the set feels a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.54,0:05:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,bit right heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.35,0:05:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The two glyphs on the left just
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.18,0:05:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,are optically smaller, and
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.65,0:05:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,consequently they feel a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.17,0:05:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,less significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.81,0:05:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if we turn on our guides, we
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.23,0:05:50.53,Default,,0,0,0,,can see that we've constrained
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.53,0:05:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,ourselves to these vertical
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.70,0:05:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,bounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.11,0:05:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's turn those off and scale
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.93,0:05:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the up optically, and that feels
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.63,0:05:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.56,0:06:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the before and the after.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.61,0:06:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the elliptical shape of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.26,0:06:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,messages and the narrow shape of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.44,0:06:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,phone have less surface area, we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.14,0:06:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,can use scale to achieve this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.90,0:06:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,optical balance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.66,0:06:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's notice another subtle
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.06,0:06:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,detail in the set here that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.52,0:06:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,helps the family of these
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.51,0:06:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,glyphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.10,0:06:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the gap in the video
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.23,0:06:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,camera and the negative space in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.24,0:06:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.02,0:06:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They share the same line weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.13,0:06:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's look at lines next.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.79,0:06:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, it looks like the glyphs
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.03,0:06:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,might have been scaled from
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.03,0:06:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,various places to fit together
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.26,0:06:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,at the size.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.97,0:06:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But because they don't share a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.53,0:06:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,consistent line weight, some
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.68,0:06:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,look more emphasized than
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.19,0:06:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,others, and this can be
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.01,0:06:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,confusing, and they just don't
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.20,0:06:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,family well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.36,0:06:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when we normalize these,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.45,0:06:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we've created a much more
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.49,0:06:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,coherent set.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.88,0:07:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the before and the after.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.11,0:07:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A subtle change like this can
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.52,0:07:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,really affect the integrity of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.98,0:07:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.72,0:07:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move on to positioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.21,0:07:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a great example here
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.46,0:07:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of optical positioning, which
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.65,0:07:19.87,Default,,0,0,0,,can sometimes be overlooked, and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.87,0:07:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we can really see it when we
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.13,0:07:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,introduce this centered circle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.54,0:07:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,around that Play glyph.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.54,0:07:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, that art is perfectly
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.80,0:07:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,centered within that space, but
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.06,0:07:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,optically, it just, it just
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.52,0:07:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,looks off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.11,0:07:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if we nudge that over a few
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.23,0:07:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,pixels to the right, we achieve
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.90,0:07:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a much more balanced result.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.33,0:07:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's the before and the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.34,0:07:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,after.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.68,0:07:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And optical positioning can
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.43,0:07:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,apply to almost any asset that's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.33,0:07:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,asymmetrical or heavier on one
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.82,0:07:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,side than the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.68,0:07:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,In this example, the share glyph
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.52,0:07:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is, again, perfectly centered
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.92,0:07:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,within that space, but it just
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.92,0:08:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like it's sitting a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.41,0:08:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,too low.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.28,0:08:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, by nudging it up a few
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.73,0:08:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,pixels, we achieve, again, a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.16,0:08:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,much more considered result.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.72,0:08:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And by the way, you can bake
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.90,0:08:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,this padding right into the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.92,0:08:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,asset.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.38,0:08:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you go to integrate,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.78,0:08:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you just center that asset
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.97,0:08:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,perfectly in that space, and any
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.34,0:08:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,adjustments that are needed be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.47,0:08:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,done with a simple [inaudible]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.58,0:08:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.30,0:08:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you're crafting your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.32,0:08:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,glyphs, build them as sets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.15,0:08:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Test them in context, and always
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.92,0:08:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,preview them on device, and this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.88,0:08:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,will help you achieve these
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.47,0:08:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,results.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.30,0:08:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you're creating
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.12,0:08:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,something from scratch, it can
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.06,0:08:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,often be hard to find a starting
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.79,0:08:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,point.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.98,0:08:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.85,0:08:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how do you get started?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.37,0:08:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at a couple of
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.14,0:08:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,considerations that can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.47,0:08:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When designing for spaces inside
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.10,0:08:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of your app, you know, such as
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.28,0:09:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,list views or buttons, consider
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.35,0:09:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the relationship between type
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.88,0:09:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and the glyphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.36,0:09:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a light type style,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.11,0:09:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,consider matching your lines to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.39,0:09:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the weight of the type.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.35,0:09:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a heavy type style,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.62,0:09:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,or more weighted, or filled
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.40,0:09:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,glyph style, it might be more
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.52,0:09:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.77,0:09:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's an example from Airbnb.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.20,0:09:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice the lines of the glyphs
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.93,0:09:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,match the fonts nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.58,0:09:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like they really
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.38,0:09:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,considered that relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.47,0:09:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,between type and glyphs, and it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.70,0:09:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,looks nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.37,0:09:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for system spaces, such as
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.57,0:09:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the Touch Bar on the Mac or Home
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.99,0:09:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,screen quick action menus on
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.12,0:09:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,iOS, and the central resource
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.39,0:09:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,can be the existing system
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.64,0:09:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.62,0:09:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,In Airbnb's Home screen quick
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,action menu, we can see the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.14,0:09:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,consistency between their custom
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.30,0:09:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,glyphs and the platforms shared
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.92,0:09:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,glyphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.63,0:09:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And notice, these glyphs are a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.96,0:09:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,bit larger and heavier than
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.47,0:10:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,their in-app counterparts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.51,0:10:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So, this is an excellent example
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.85,0:10:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of craftsmanship here by Airbnb.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.98,0:10:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we have templates on the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.32,0:10:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,human interface guidelines to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.92,0:10:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,help you match optical weight
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.66,0:10:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,lines and positioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.88,0:10:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This will help you save time, be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.35,0:10:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,harmonious with the established
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.71,0:10:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,design language, and you can
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,even output your assets directly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.99,0:10:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,from these templates, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.75,0:10:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.76,0:10:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.44,0:10:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've gone over a bunch of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.76,0:10:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,things here in a short period of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.13,0:10:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.35,0:10:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do a quick recap.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.63,0:10:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,When conceptualizing a glyph,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.97,0:10:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,simplify and think globally.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.87,0:10:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When crafting them, build them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.13,0:10:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,as sets and test them in context
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.84,0:10:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to make them feel like a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.33,0:10:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider the relationship of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.90,0:10:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,type in your glyphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.19,0:10:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, adapt your assets
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.42,0:11:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for system spaces.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.82,0:11:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I hope that these tips will
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.27,0:11:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,help you build more effective
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.79,0:11:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and delightful experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.28,0:11:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But wait a minute, something
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.37,0:11:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,looks wrong here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.24,0:11:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.93,0:11:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
